{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove national insurance and means test for ESA for disabled people",
        "additional_details": "As someone who is chronically ill and disabled I have not been able to work enough hours to meet the national insurance requirement, and do not meet the means test.\r\n\r\nThe Government should remove the national insurance and means test for claiming ESA for chronically ill or disabled people, who should be able to claim this support when it is needed.\r\n \r\nI worked part time even when struggling as I didn't want to rely on benefits, but now I need this support am not entitled to it.",
        "background": "In order to get Employment and Support Allowance (ESA) you need to have paid enough national insurance credits or meet a means test.\r\n",
